The paper focuses on unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The proposed method involves optimizing a contrastive loss to better align target samples with the source domain, which is a common technique in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions using Maximum Mean Discrepancy (MMD) to match features between source and target samples, which is a common technique in domain adaptation research. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
